        "faq_MRYAgR": {
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I color hair extensions?",
            "body": "We recommend keeping our hair extensions in their original colour. Deciding to color or tone them falls entirely under your responsibility and risk. Remember, these extensions have already undergone chemical processing. Choosing to alter their color could compromise their integrity and appearance. If a color change is a must, consider dyeing the client’s natural hair to match the extensions before installation."
          }
        },
        "faq_J8cExN": {
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does T and DD mean in your color ranges?",
            "body": "When a color starts with T it means that the color is a root stretch color. For example, if the color is T5-9/613 this means that it will be a 9/613 mix with a root stretch of color 5. Our root stretch length is around 2-3 inches depending on the overall length of the hair. When a color starts with DD it means that the color is a dip-dye color. For example, if the color is DD2/6 this means that the top half of the hair is color 2 followed by a color 6 on the bottom half of the hair."
          }
        },
        "faq_TJaCdk": {
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the difference between the Super and Standard color rings?",
            "body": "Our Super Ring features larger swatches, we recommend this ring for Salons and large workspaces. Our standard color ring has smaller swatches and is more suitable for those who may have a smaller workspace or are mobile."
          }
        }
      }
    },
